Here's a Java solution to the problem that uses logarithm to check if n is a power of three:

```
class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }
        double x = Math.log(n) / Math.log(3);
        return Math.pow(3, Math.round(x)) == n;
    }
}
```

The `Math.log(n) / Math.log(3)` expression calculates the logarithm of n base 3, which gives us the exponent x in the equation n == 3^x. We then round x to the nearest integer using `Math.round(x)` and check if 3 raised to that integer power is equal to n. If it is, then n is a power of three and we return true; otherwise, we return false.

